body:
Good medium-starter task

#2326 will add support for queue slices which in some cases use unbounded.  It is also legal to use $ to refer to the maximum index of an array, e.g.

   reg [3:0] foo;
   reg [3:1] bar_is_foo_3_to_1 = foo[$:1];

Add appropriate packed and unpacked and multidimensional cases that use $ and update (probably) V3WidthSel and V3Width to support these - basically the Unbounded would be seen and the existing array bound which is then known would replace the $.
